# LLMDB Basics

```elixir
Mix.install([
  {:llm_db, "~> 2026.1"},
])
```

## Intro / Configuration

[LLMDB](https://github.com/agentjido/llm_db) is a support library for  [ReqLLM](https://github.com/agentjido/llm_db), a database of LLM providers.

```elixir
LLMDB.providers() |> Enum.map(&(&1.id))
```

```elixir
LLMDB.providers() |> Enum.filter(&(&1.id == :anthropic)) |> List.first()
```

```elixir
_models = LLMDB.models(:anthropic) |> Enum.map(&(&1.model))
```

Model details are stored in the package: including pricing, capabilitites, modalities, and token limits. These can be re-synced from [models.dev](https://models.dev) via a `mix` task (`mix req_llm.model_sync`) outside of a Livebook context.

```elixir
# Show the details of a specific model, and store it for usage throughout the Livebook
{:ok, _model} = LLMDB.model(:anthropic, "claude-haiku-4-5")
```

